quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  17,105,"And with truth We have sent it down and with truth it descended. And We did not send you but as a bearer of good tidings and as a warner."
  17,106,"And We have divided the Qur'an in portions, so that you may recite it to the people gradually, and We have revealed it little by little."
  17,107,"Say, "Believe it or do not believe it; when it is recited to those who were given knowledge before it, they fall down on their faces in prostration"
  17,108,"and say, 'Pure is our Lord. Certainly, the word of our Lord is sure to be done.""
  17,109,"And they fall down on their faces weeping and it increases them in the humbleness of heart."
  17,110,"Say, "Call (Him by the name of) Allah or Ar-Rahman, in whichever way you call, His are the best names." And do not be (too) loud in your Salah nor be (too) low in it, and seek a way in between."
  17,111,"And say, 'Praise belongs to Allah who has neither taken to Him a son, nor is there any partner to Him in His kingdom, nor is anyone (needed) to protect Him because of (any) weakness. And proclaim His greatness, an open proclamation."
  18,1,"Praise belongs to Allah who has sent down to His servant the Book and allowed no crookedness in it,"
  18,2,"a straightforward Book to warn of a severe punishment from Him, and to give glad tidings to the believers who do righteous deeds that they will have a good reward (Paradise)"
  18,3,"where they will dwell forever,"
  18,4,"and to warn those who have said that Allah has taken to Him-self a son,"